cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on object symmetry detection. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The proposed approach, SRN, involves residual units, which are a popular technique in deep learning and machine learning (ML) research, making cs.LG and cs.MM possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of multiple scales, which is a common technique in neural networks and ML, making cs.NE a possible sub-category as well.
